---
import '../styles/global.css';

const updatedAt = '23 May 2026';
---

<html lang="id">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Privacy Policy - AI Threads</title>
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Privacy Policy untuk AI Threads, termasuk penggunaan data untuk integrasi Buffer API."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <main class="public-page">
      <article class="panel public-document">
        <p class="muted" style="margin: 0 0 8px;">Last updated: {updatedAt}</p>
        <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

        <p>
          AI Threads helps users generate, review, schedule, and publish social media content.
          This policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how users can
          request access or deletion.
        </p>

        <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
        <p>
          We may collect account information such as name, email address, login session data,
          generated content drafts, publishing schedules, Buffer profile identifiers, and activity
          logs needed to operate the application.
        </p>

        <h2>Buffer API Data</h2>
        <p>
          If you connect Buffer, we use Buffer access credentials only to retrieve connected
          profiles and submit content that you choose to publish or schedule. We do not sell Buffer
          data, and we do not use Buffer data for advertising.
        </p>

        <h2>How We Use Information</h2>
        <p>
          We use collected information to authenticate users, save drafts, generate content,
          schedule posts, send approved content to Buffer, troubleshoot errors, and maintain audit
          logs for application activity.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
        <p>
          We share data only with service providers required to run the product, including Supabase
          for database storage, OpenRouter for AI generation when requested, and Buffer for
          publishing or scheduling approved content.
        </p>

        <h2>Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          Drafts, settings, schedules, and logs are retained while the account is active or as
          needed for operational records. Users may request deletion of their data.
        </p>

        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>
          We use server-side storage for API credentials and authentication cookies for user
          sessions. No system can guarantee absolute security, but we take reasonable steps to
          protect access to application data.
        </p>

        <h2>Your Choices</h2>
        <p>
          You may request access, correction, or deletion of your personal information. You may
          also disconnect Buffer by removing the stored Buffer account configuration.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For privacy requests, contact the application owner at the email address provided in the
          Buffer developer application or deployment owner profile.
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>
